Three people have died after they were knocked down by a vehicle in Salgaa on the Nakuru/Eldoret highway. One person died on the spot while two others died enroute to the hospital. Mr James Kirui, an eye witness, said the Toyota Land Cruiser was skidding before knocking the three. The victims are a truck driver and mechanics who were repairing a tyre puncture. Salgaa Traffic base Commander Walter Kiptala confirmed the accident and said investigations to establish the cause of the incident are under way. The wreckage was towed to Salgaa police station.  